hich%20envisages%20the%20holding%20of%20general%20election%20and%20state%20Assembly%20elections%20simultaneously%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Findia-news%2Fkovind-to-hold-first-meeting-of-one-nation-one-election-panel-today-123090600359_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fkovind-to-hold-first-meeting-of-one-nation-one-election-panel-today-123090600359_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fkovind-to-hold-first-meeting-of-one-nation-one-election-panel-today-123090600359_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World%20Cup%3A%20Fans%20scamper%20for%20the%20elusive%20India-Pakistan%20ticket%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693984220000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103422630%2Cimgsize-123812.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Ficc-world-cup-2023-fans-scamper-for-the-elusive-india-pakistan-match-ticket%2Farticleshow%2F103422399.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20much-anticipated%20showdown%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20the%20ICC%20Cricket%20World%20Cup%202023%20is%20scheduled%20for%20October%2014th%20at%20Ahmedabad's%20Narendra%20Modi%20Stadium%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20and%20cricket%20enthusiasts%20from%20all%20corners%20of%20India%20are%20sparing%20no%20effort%20in%20their%20quest%20to%20secure%20a%20ticket%20for%20the%20electrifying%20match%20set%20to%20unfold%20in%20the%20world's%20biggest%20cricket%20stadium.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Ficc-world-cup%2Ficc-world-cup-2023-fans-scamper-for-the-elusive-india-pakistan-match-ticket%2Farticleshow%2F103422399.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anil%20Sharma%3A%20Jr%20NTR%20can%20play%20Tara%20Singh%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693984124000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103422725%2Cimgsize-30168.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fanil-sharma-feels-jr-ntr-can-play-sunny-deols-role-of-tara-singh-says-he-has-an-image-that-could-work%2Farticleshow%2F103422725.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F103422725.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDirector%20Anil%20Sharma%2C%20who%20is%20enjoying%20the%20success%20of%20'Gadar%202'%2C%20revealed%20that%20he%20would%20cast%20Jr%20NTR%20if%20the%20film%20was%20made%20today.%20He%20praised%20Jr%20NTR's%20image%20and%20said%20he%20could%20fit%20the%20role%20of%20Tara%20Singh.%20However%2C%20he%20did%20not%20mention%20anyone%20for%20the%20role%20of%20Sakeena.%20Anil%20also%20mentioned%20that%20he%20prefers%20not%20to%20respond%20to%20trolls.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Opinion%3A%20Simultaneous%20Elections%20-%20Mother%20of%20all%20Democratic%20Reforms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20dead%20against%20is%20the%20Chalta%20Hai%20attitude%20that%20has%20become%20the%20mainspring%20of%20Status-Quo-ist%20approach.%20This%20approach%20is%20age-old%20and%20omnipresent.%20Hardly%20surprising%20then%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20has%20once%20again%20become%20a%20major%20point%20of%20debates%20and%20discussions.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5CnUnderstandably%2C%20there%20is%20quite%20a%20buzz%20about%20the%20Ramnath%20Kovind-led%20committee%20tasked%20with%20submitting%20its%20report%20on%20Simultaneous%20Elections.%20(Perhaps%20'simultaneous%20elections'%20is%20a%20more%20appropriate%20way%20of%20describing%20the%20One%20Nation-One%20Election%20idea).%20As%20expected%2C%20most%20opposition%20parties%20are%20attributing%20motives%20and%20spreading%20canards.%20Yet%20they%20can't%20deny%20the%20very%20merit%20behind%20holding%20elections%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20simultaneously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECountries%20like%20Sweden%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Belgium%2C%20France%20and%20Italy%2C%20among%20others%2C%20are%20popular%20examples%20to%20illustrate%20the%20benefits%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20municipalities%2C%20state%20assemblies%20and%20parliament.%20This%20key%20democratic%20reform%20has%20enabled%20these%20countries%20to%20reduce%20their%20election%20spend%20considerably%2C%20consolidate%20the%20feeling%20of%20national%20identity%20and%20integrity%2C%20and%20above%20all%2C%20stabilise%20the%20state%20machinery%20and%20governance%20with%20minimal%20disruption%20of%20public%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20we%20had%20already%20implemented%20simultaneous%20elections%20between%201952-1967%2C%20almost%20uninterrupted.%20This%20was%20discontinued%20after%201967%20as%20the%20Fifth%20Lok%20Sabha%20Elections%20were%20held%20(in%201971)%20before%20schedule%20(1972).%20So%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20unprecedented%20or%20impractical%20about%20this%20proposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20to%20power%20in%202014%2C%20PM%20Modi%20had%20advocated%20the%20need%20for%20this%20key%20reform.%20Former%20President%20Pranab%20Mukherjee%20also%20had%20supported%20this%20idea.%20On%20December%2017%202015%2C%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20on%20Personnel%2C%20Public%20Grievances%2C%20Law%20and%20Justice%20submitted%20its%20report%20titled%20'Feasibility%20of%20Holding%20Simultaneous%20Elections%20to%20House%20of%20People%20(Lok%20Sabha)%20and%20State%20Legislative%20Assemblies'.%20The%20committee%20noted%20that%20the%20simulations%20elections%20would%20enable%20the%20government%20to%20reduce%3A%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(A)%20The%20massive%20election%20expenditure%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(B)%20The%20burden%20on%20crucial%20manpower%20that%20is%20deployed%20during%20election%20time%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E(C)%20The%20policy%20paralysis%20that%20results%20from%20the%20imposition%20of%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20during%20election%20time%3B%20and%3Cbr%3E%5Cn(D)%20The%20impact%20on%20essential%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%2C%20to%20start%20with%2C%20it%20is%20educative%20to%20have%20a%20look%20at%20the%20present%20situation.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20were%20held%20over%20several%20phases%20in%20the%20months%20of%20April%20and%20May.%20The%20same%20year%2C%20state%20assembly%20elections%20were%20conducted%20for%20eight%20states%20-%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Arunachal%20Pradesh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%2C%20Jharkhand%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Odisha%2C%20and%20Sikkim.%20In%202020%2C%20the%20Delhi%20and%20Bihar%20selections%20were%20held.%20In%202021%2C%20five%20states%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Puducherry%20and%20Assam%2C%20voted.%20In%202022%2C%20seven%20state%20assemblies%20were%20elected%20-%20Punjab%2C%20Goa%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttarakhand%2C%20and%20Manipur%2C%20followed%20by%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20and%20Gujarat.%20Later%20in%202023%2C%20Karnataka%20voted.%20This%20is%20barring%20the%20other%20countless%20elections%20and%20by-elections%20to%20local%20bodies%2C%20both%20urban%20and%20rural.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20let's%20talk%20about%20the%20massive%20election%20expenditure.%20Today%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20spends%20not%20less%20than%20Rs.%2010%2C000%20crore%20on%20just%20one%20round%20of%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20elections%2C%20while%20the%20estimated%20cost%20of%20simultaneous%20elections%20is%20about%20Rs.%204%2C500%20crore.%20One%20certainly%20cannot%20ignore%20the%20fact%20that%20simultaneous%20elections%20would%20help%20save%20our%20national%20resources%20to%20the%20tune%20of%20Rs.5%2C500%20crore.%20Considering%20that%20this%20amount%20equals%20half%20the%20annual%20budget%20of%20some%20of%20the%20smaller%20northeastern%20states%2C%20this%20saving%20is%20not%20insignificant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20NITI%20Aayog%20paper%20says%20with%20the%20passage%20of%20time%2C%20conducting%20elections%20too%20is%20becoming%20expensive.%20Also%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20elections%20and%20the%20client-patron%20relation%20between%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20electorate%20also%20pushes%20up%20the%20expenditure%2C%20which%20more%20often%20than%20not%20goes%20unrecorded%2C%20A%20case%20in%20point%20is%20the%20distribution%20of%20goods%2C%20liquor%2C%20and%20money.%20It%20has%20been%20argued%20that%20such%20incentives%20and%20bribes%20are%20the%20main%20source%20of%20black%20money%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20crucial%20point%20is%20about%20saving%20on%20Human%20Resources.%20In%20any%20general%20election%2C%20the%20nation%20sees%20over%2010%20million%20personnel%20involved%20as%20polling%20officials%20across%209%2C30%2C000%20polling%20stations%20across%20the%20country%2C%20which%20necessities%20deployment%20of%20over%201%2C349%20companies%20(each%20company%20has%20100%20soldiers)%20of%20CAPF%20(Central%20Armed%20Police%20Force).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20important%20point%20is%20about%20the%20policy%20paralysis%20caused%20by%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct.%20In%202017%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20had%20brought%20out%20a%20discussion%20paper%20developed%20by%20Bibek%20Debroy%20and%20Kishore%20Desai.%20The%20discussion%20paper%20has%20argued%20comprehensively%20for%20simultaneous%20elections%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20in%20India.%20Its%20major%20argument%20hinges%20upon%20the%20issue%20of%20governance%20and%20the%20virtual%20stalemate%20of%20day-to-day%20administration%20in%20some%20part%20of%20the%20country%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20poll%20code.%20There%20are%20plenty%20of%20examples%20of%20how%20the%20spirit%20behind%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20is%20forgotten%20as%20the%20provision%20is%20stretched%20too%20far.%20For%20example%2C%20when%20elections%20to%20the%20Teachers%20Constituency%20of%20a%20legislative%20council%20are%20to%20be%20held%2C%20the%20code%20of%20conduct%20is%20applied%20to%20the%20entire%20revenue%20division.%20In%20a%20situation%20like%20this%2C%20ironically%2C%20even%20a%20small%20village%20with%20no%20registered%20voter%20for%20Teachers'%20Constituency%20suffers%20as%20all%20development%20activities%20are%20stalled%20for%20at%20least%20three-four%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20as%20pointed%20out%20by%20the%20NITI%20Aayog%20paper%2C%20in%20the%20last%2030%20years%3B%20there%20has%20not%20been%20a%20single%20year%20without%20an%20election%20to%20either%20any%20of%20the%20state%20assemblies%20or%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20or%20both.%20The%20time%20consumed%20by%20the%20preps%20for%20every%20election%20afflicts%20not%20only%20governance%20but%20also%20national%20development.%20Not%20for%20no%20reason%2C%20senior%20BJP%20leader%20LK%20Advani%20had%20once%20observed%20that%20multiple%20polls%20make%20us%20a%20country%20that%20is%20perennially%20in%20election%20mode.%20Besides%2C%20election%20after%20election%20also%20forces%20the%20political%20class%20to%20typically%20think%20in%20terms%20of%20electoral%20gains%20rather%20than%20robust%20policy%20implementation.%20There%20have%20been%20multiple%20instances%20in%20the%20past%20where%20the%20governments%20have%20preferred%20to%20postpone%20much-needed%20structural%20reforms%20as%20elections%20were%20just%20round%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20in%20the%20opposition%2C%20as%20also%20media%2C%20rush%20to%20proclaim%20that%20the%20idea%20is%20impracticable.%20They%20are%20advised%20to%20read%20a%202015%20report%20by%20the%20standing%20committee.%20This%20committee%2C%20headed%20at%20that%20time%20by%20EM%20Sudarsana%20Natchiappan%2C%20a%20Congress%20MP%2C%20had%20given%20a%20highly%20studied%20and%20structured%20report.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20report%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20Committee%20noted%20that%20the%20Representation%20of%20People%20Act%2C%201951%20permits%20the%20Election%20Commission%20to%20notify%20general%20elections%20six%20months%20prior%20to%20the%20end%20of%20the%20terms%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20the%20committee%20recommended%20that%20in%20order%20to%20hold%20early%20elections%20to%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20legislative%C2%A0assemblies%2C%20one%20of%20two%20conditions%20must%20be%20met%3A%20(i)%20a%20motion%20for%20an%20early%20general%20election%20must%20be%20supported%20by%20at%20least%20two-thirds%20of%20all%20members%20of%20the%20House%3B%20or%20(ii)%20a%20no%20confidence%20motion%20must%20be%20passed%20by%20the%20House%2C%20and%20no%20alternative%20government%20should%20be%20confirmed%20within%2014%20days%20of%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20no%20trust%20motion.%20This%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20has%20also%20advocated%20elections%20in%20two%20phases%2C%20in%20which%20half%20the%20assemblies%20could%20have%20elections%20along%20with%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20other%20half%20at%20the%20midterm%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20as%20opposition%20parties%20are%20concerned%2C%20they%20need%20to%20rise%20above%20partisan%20considerations.%20Simultaneous%20elections%20need%20not%20be%20seen%20as%20either%20a%20BJP%20agenda%20or%20a%20Modi%20government%20agenda.%20This%20Mother%20of%20All%20Democratic%20Reforms%20needs%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20our%20national%20agenda.%20If%20major%20political%20parties%20honestly%20think%20about%20this%2C%20consensus%20should%20not%20be%20all%20that%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVinay%20Sahasrabuddhe%20is%20former%20MP%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20columnist%2C%20besides%20being%20President%20of%20Indian%20Council%20of%20Cultural%20Relations%20(ICCR)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693983900000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-11%2Fmpbfnv4_election-generic-afp650_625x300_02_November_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-simultaneous-elections-mother-of-all-democratic-reforms-4364017%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20thing%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20dead%20against%20is%20the%20Chalta%20Hai%20attitude%20that%20has%20become%20the%20mainspring%20of%20Status-Quo-ist%20approach.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-simultaneous-elections-mother-of-all-democratic-reforms-4364017%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-simultaneous-elections-mother-of-all-democratic-reforms-4364017%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-simultaneous-elections-mother-of-all-democratic-reforms-4364017%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Capital%20Chaos%3A%20Surprise%20Traffic%20Drill%20Causes%20Jams%2C%20Confusion%20Among%20Commuters%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F06115247%2FIndia_Gate._New_Delhi_India_23497630455.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20capital%20came%20to%20a%20standstill%20for%20a%20few%20hours%20after%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fdelhi-news%2Fdelhi-police-s-unannounced-rehearsal-causes-chaos-on-city-roads-commuters-left-frustrated-and-confused-101693936194594.html%5C%22%3EDelhi%20police%20conducted%20an%20unplanned%20traffic%20drill%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Tuesday%20morning%20(September%205)%20in%20preparation%20fo