%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%20and%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20introducing%20them%2C%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%201860%20to%202023%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20criminal%20justice%20system%20functioned%20as%20per%20the%20laws%20made%20by%20the%20British.%20With%20these%20three%20laws%20there%20will%20be%20a%20major%20change%20in%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20in%20this%20country%E2%80%9D%2C%20finally%20freeing%20us%20from%20colonial%20legacies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Bills%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20the%20standing%20committee%20on%20home%20affairs%20for%20further%20examination%2C%20they%20are%20being%20touted%20by%20the%20government%20and%20its%20ideologues%20as%20effecting%20%E2%80%98decolonisation%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20legal%20and%20criminal%20justice%20system%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELegal%20experts%20are%20still%20studying%20the%20new%20Bills%20and%20grappling%20with%20the%20introduced%20changes%2C%20but%20most%20analyses%20so%20far%20suggest%20that%20not%20much%20has%20been%20changed%20in%20substance.%20Apart%20from%20naming%20the%20bills%20in%20Hindi%20and%20calling%20it%20%E2%80%98imbibing%20the%20laws%20with%20Indian%20soul%E2%80%99%2C%20most%20changes%20consist%20of%20shifting%20around%20sections%20of%20the%20existing%20laws%20and%20some%20semantic%20changes%20in%20construction%20of%20sentences.%20A%20Turnitin%20(plagiarism-detector%20software)%20report%20suggests%2083%25%20overlap%20between%20the%20IPC%20and%20BNS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fas-laws-expand-their-reach-in-india-political-freedoms-shrink%5C%22%3E%20As%20Laws%20Expand%20Their%20Reach%20in%20India%2C%20Political%20Freedoms%20Shrink%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20major%20planks%20of%20this%20claimed%20decolonisation%20is%20removal%20of%20section%20124(a)%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition.%20However%2C%20on%20closer%20scrutiny%20this%20claim%20falls%20flat%20as%20a%20similar%20offence%20is%20introduced%20through%20section%20150%20in%20the%20BNS.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20this%20section%20is%20even%20more%20vague%20and%20much%20wider%20in%20scope%20than%20the%20IPC%20section%20on%20Sedition%20as%20it%20includes%20even%20intention%20in%20its%20ambit%20without%20adequate%20explanations.%20The%20vaguer%20the%20definition%2C%20the%20more%20power%20the%20state%20has%20to%20clampdown%20on%20the%20perceived%20threats%20to%20itself%20and%20brand%20any%20dissent%20as%20anti-national.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20deletion%20of%20the%20terms%20such%20as%20lunatic%20and%20of%20unsound%20mind%20and%20making%20investigative%20and%20trial%20process%20time%20bound%20in%20the%20BNSS%20is%20being%20celebrated%20for%20shedding%20colonial%20legacies%2C%20the%20BNSS%20has%20brought%20in%20changes%20expanding%20the%20powers%20of%20police%20and%20the%20executive%20tremendously.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20changes%20include%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebroadening%20the%20scope%20of%20investigative%20powers%20under%20search%20and%20seizure%2C%20ability%20to%20get%20samples%20from%20a%20larger%20set%20of%20people%2C%20curbing%20the%20power%20of%20commutation%2C%20bringing%20handcuffs%20back%2C%20making%20it%20more%20difficult%20to%20prosecute%20government%20officials%2C%20and%20increased%20scope%20of%20the%20remand%20procedure.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EApart%20from%20their%20individual%20effects%20of%20further%20curbing%20civil%20liberties%2C%20I%20want%20to%20focus%20on%20the%20cumulative%20impact%20and%20political%20import%20such%20expansion%20of%20the%20power%20and%20impunity%20of%20the%20state.%20And%20that%20is%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20matter%20here%20%E2%80%93%20the%20power%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20citizens%2C%20the%20government%20and%20the%20governed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20decolonisation%20is%20a%20much-contested%20term%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20discipline%20of%20History%20where%20I%20come%20from%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20fundamentally%20understood%20as%20the%20alteration%20of%20the%20power%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20governed%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20latter%2C%20their%20transition%20from%20subjects%20to%20citizens.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fvideo-karan-thapar-election-commission-gautam-bhatia%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Modi%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20EC%20Bill%20Undermines%20Its%20Independence%2C%20Should%20Be%20Struck%20Down%20if%20Passed%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20colonial%20state%20and%20its%20forms%20of%20government%2C%20apart%20from%20extractive%20relationships%2C%20were%20characterised%20by%20rule%20by%20force%20and%20subjection%20of%20populations.%20The%20interests%20of%20the%20state%20trumped%20the%20interests%20and%20rights%20of%20the%20governed%2C%20with%20substantial%20impunity%20and%20non-accountability%20of%20the%20state%20to%20the%20subject%20populations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20also%20reflected%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20laws%2C%20especially%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20which%20was%20characterised%20by%20wide%20powers%20of%20policing%20and%20arrest%20with%20an%20emphasis%20on%20punishment%20and%20disciplining%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98errant%E2%80%99%20subjects%20rather%20than%20justice.%20Hence%2C%20any%20effective%20decolonisation%20would%20entail%20a%20shift%20in%20this%20relationship%20in%20terms%20of%20devolving%20substantial%20power%20to%20the%20citizens%20and%20their%20participation%20in%20modes%20of%20governance%20and%20making%20of%20laws%20which%20govern%20their%20lives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20proposed%20changes%20further%20entrench%20the%20power%20relationship%20between%20the%20state%20and%20citizens%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20former%2C%20even%20the%20process%20of%20their%20formulation%20and%20introduction%20in%20the%20parliament%20lack%20public%20participation%20and%20transparency.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20terms%20of%20reference%20of%20the%20Committee%20for%20Reforms%20in%20Criminal%20Law%2C%20which%20was%20tasked%20with%20drafting%20of%20these%20Bills%20May%202020%2C%20were%20never%20made%20public.%20Further%2C%20it%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farticle-14.com%2Fpost%2Fhome-minister-amit-shah-says-sedition-is-dead-but-its-replacement-is-more-fearsome-than-the-colonial-law-ever-was-64d99ff8dc0d8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20lacked%20diversity%20and%20representative%20voices%20of%20people%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20across%20disciplines%20and%20capacities%2C%20and%20the%20committee%20was%20given%20just%20six%20months%20to%20overhaul%20three%20major%20criminal%20laws.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20lack%20continued%20in%20the%20process%20of%20introduction%20of%20these%20Bills.%20They%20were%20introduced%20on%20the%20last%20day%20of%20the%20session%20leaving%20no%20chance%20for%20any%20debate%20or%20discussion%20about%20the%20monumental%20changes%20they%20are%20supposed%20to%20bring%20to%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20in%20this%20country%20thus%20affecting%20the%20lives%20of%201.3%20billion%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20not%20just%20these%20bills%2C%20but%20this%20government%E2%80%99s%20recurring%20pattern%20of%20formulating%20Bills%20and%20laws%20without%20wider%20public%20consultations%20and%20debates%2C%20ignoring%20g%20critical%20opinions%2C%20and%20passing%20laws%20in%20haste%20without%20adequate%20discussions%20even%20in%20the%20Parliament.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20also%20been%20a%20constant%20dilution%20of%20measures%20of%20participation%2C%20transparency%2C%20and%20accountability%20of%20the%20state%2C%20rendering%20citizens%20more%20vulnerable%20in%20front%20of%20the%20state.%20A%20prime%20example%20of%20this%20is%20the%20recently%20passed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-lies-beneath-the-pr-blitz-on-the-new-data-protection-act%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520a%2520hasty%2520sweeping%2520stride%2Cpassing%2520by%2520the%2520Rajya%2520Sabha.%5C%22%3EData%20Protection%20Bill%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20dilutes%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%20substantially%20and%20entrenches%20executive%20control%20over%20data.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELaws%20are%20always%20embedded%20in%20wider%20networks%20of%20meaning%20and%20context%20in%20society.%20It%20derives%20its%20power%20not%20just%20from%20the%20written%20texts%20but%20d%20web%20of%20power%20relations%20in%20the%20society.%20The%20criminal%20justice%20system%20represents%20the%20most%20direct%20relationship%20of%20power%20between%20people%20and%20the%20state%20as%20an%20individual%20is%20pitted%20against%20the%20whole%20might%20of%20the%20state%20as%20an%20accused.%20So%20even%20with%20some%20%E2%80%98progressive%20changes%20in%20the%20new%20Bills%2C%20they%20are%20very%20far%20from%20effecting%20any%20real%20decolonisation%20as%20long%20as%20the%20text%20of%20governing%20remains%20entrenched%20in%20the%20authoritarian%20colonial%20power%20relations%20of%20putting%20state%20over%20people.%20Changing%20the%20names%20to%20Hindi%20will%20not%20free%20us%20from%20colonial%20legacies.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENatasha%C2%A0%3Cspan%3ENarwal%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20a%20feminist%20activist%20based%20in%20Delhi%20and%20Haryana%2C%20is%20currently%20associated%20with%C2%A0%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Pinjratod%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22htt