an%201%2C800%20miles%20to%20reach%20the%20site.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETwo%20helicopters%20were%20deployed%20from%20the%20vessel's%20deck%20to%20retrieve%20the%20sick%20researcher.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAustralia's%20Antarctic%20research%20agency%20undertook%20a%20daring%20rescue%20mission%20this%20month%20after%20one%20of%20its%20Antarctic%20expeditioners%20required%20urgent%20medical%20care%20while%20living%20at%20a%20remote%20research%20station%202%2C400%20miles%20due%20south%20of%20Perth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.antarctica.gov.au%2Fabout-us%2Faustralian-antarctic-program%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustralian%20Antarctic%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%20employed%20the%20RSV%20Nuyina%2C%20a%20state-of-the-art%20research%20and%20supply%20vessel%2C%20to%20travel%20the%20more%20than%201%2C800%20miles%20between%20the%20ship's%20home%20base%20of%20Hobart%20on%20the%20island%20state%20of%20Tasmania%20and%20the%20Casey%20research%20center%20located%20on%20the%20perch%20of%20a%20large%20Antarctic%20ice%20cap%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20agency%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rescue%20operation%20came%20as%20the%20Southern%20Hemisphere%20marked%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20spring%20season%20with%20temperatures%20hovering%20just%20around%2010%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20earliest%20we've%20ever%20gone%20to%20an%20Antarctic%20station%20%E2%80%94%20just%20a%20day%20or%20two%20after%20the%20official%20end%20of%20winter%2C%26quot%3B%20Robb%20Clifton%2C%20the%20acting%20general%20manager%20of%20operations%20and%20logistics%20at%20the%20Australian%20Antarctic%20Division%2C%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2023-09-04%2Fantarctic-expeditioner-medical-evacuation-from-casey-station%2F102812494%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAustralian%20Broadcasting%20Corp%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BBut%20it's%20still%20very%20much%20winter%20in%20Antarctica.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.antarctica.gov.au%2Fantarctic-operations%2Fstations%2Fcasey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECasey%20research%20station%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20the%20closest%20permanent%20Antarctic%20station%20to%20Australia%2C%20is%20home%20to%20only%20about%2020%20people%20during%20the%20winter%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20station's%20expeditioners%20had%20a%26quot%3Bdeveloping%20medical%20condition%26quot%3B%20that%20required%20specialist%20care%20back%20in%20Australia%2C%20the%20agency%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20an%20email%20statement%20to%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20sent%20the%20Nuyina%20from%20Hobart%20to%20Casey%20last%20week%2C%20using%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.antarctica.gov.au%2Fabout-antarctica%2Fhistory%2Ftransportation%2Fshipping%2Frsv-nuyina%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehalf-a-billion%20dollar%3C%2Fa%3E%20vessel%20to%20cut%20through%20miles%20of%20deep%20sea%20ice.%20The%20ship%20was%20able%20to%20reach%20a%20location%20about%2078%20nautical%20miles%20from%20Casey%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20agency%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20Nuyina%20reached%20proximity%20to%20the%20research%20site%2C%20two%20helicopters%20carrying%20a%20medical%20retrieval%20team%20were%20deployed%20from%20the%20vessel's%20deck.%20The%20aircraft%20took%20a%20nearly%20hour%20long%20flight%20to%20get%20to%20Casey%20and%20retrieve%20the%20sick%20expeditioner%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Australian%20Antarctic%20Program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClifton%20said%20it%20was%20agreeable%20weather%20that%20ultimately%20allowed%20the%20two%20helicopters%20to%20make%20the%20final%20stretch%20of%20the%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20first%20phase%20of%20the%20evacuation%20was%20performed%20safely%20and%20successfully%20and%20the%20ship%20is%20now%20on%20the%20return%20voyage%20to%20Hobart%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20map%20shows%20the%20distance%20the%20Nuyina%20travelled%20between%20Hobart%20and%20Casey%20research%20center.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f7b94d1b7ced0019c8a340%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20map%20shows%20the%20distance%20the%20Nuyina%20travelled%20between%20Hobart%20and%20Casey%20research%20center.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20AAD%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency%20declined%20to%20offer%20details%20about%20the%20evacuated%20expeditioner's%20current%20health%2C%20but%20Clifton%20said%20they%20would%20be%20looked%20after%20in%20the%20Nuyina's%20medical%20facility%20staffed%20by%20polar%20medicine%20doctors%20and%20hospital%20medical%20staff%20on%20the%20journey%20back%20to%20Hobart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Nuyina%20is%20due%20back%20in%20Hobart%20sometime%20next%20week%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20weather%20conditions%20in%20the%20Southern%20Ocean%2C%20an%20agency%20spokesperson%20said.%20The%20icebreaker%2C%20which%20cost%20%24528%20million%20to%20design%20and%20build%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.antarctica.gov.au%2Fnuyina%2Fabout%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Australian%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20introduced%20in%202021%20to%20conduct%20science%20missions%20and%20transport%20researchers%20and%20supplies%20to%20Antarctica.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20really%20only%20able%20to%20attempt%20it%20because%20of%20the%20fantastic%20capabilities%20the%20Nuyina%20gives%20us%20in%20terms%20of%20icebreaking%20and%20aircraft%20capability%2C%26quot%3B%20Clifton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantarctica-australia-icebreaker-rescue-mission-sick-researcher-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693958500000%2C%22visual