3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Japan%20only%20exports%20a%20limited%20amount%20of%20Wagyu%20beef%2C%20most%20of%20the%20so-called%20Wagyu%20eaten%20by%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20is%20not%20exactly%20up%20to%20the%20same%20standard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20US%2C%20ranchers%20interbreed%20Wagyu%20cows%20with%20hardier%20stock%2C%20and%20government%20regulations%20only%20require%20one%20parent%20of%20a%20cow%20to%20be%20Wagyu%20(with%2093.7%25%20genetic%20match)%20in%20order%20to%20market%20its%20meat%20as%20Wagyu%20beef.%20That%20beef%20would%20have%20just%20a%2046.9%25%20genetic%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20fast%20food%20chain%20Arby's%20advertised%20a%20Wagyu%20burger%2C%20the%20patty%20was%20made%20with%20just%2051%25%20American%20Wagyu%20plus%2049%25%20regular%20ground%20beef%2C%20so%20only%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20meat%20was%20genetically%20Wagyu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20true%20Wagyu%20is%20too%20tender%20to%20make%20for%20a%20good%20hamburger%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECoffee%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221420%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coffee%20beans%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f787c6781926001911a74c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221063%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DK0OtGIPRcAs%26t%3D1340s%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECoffee%20is%20big%2C%20big%2C%20big%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20historically%20it%20has%20been%20cut%20with%20anything%20that's%20brown%3A%20burnt%20paper%2C%20burnt%20corn%2C%20sawdust%2C%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20Larry%20Olmstead%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGround%20coffee%20has%20also%20been%20augmented%20with%20ground%20acorns%2C%20barley%2C%20and%20wheat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhole-bean%20coffee%20naturally%20tends%20to%20have%20less%20filler%2C%20but%20the%20challenges%20of%20growing%20and%20cultivating%20large%20amounts%20of%20it%20can%20lead%20to%20significant%20differences%20in%20quality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20some%201%2C500%20coffee%20cherries%20to%20make%201%20pound%20of%20beans%2C%20and%20the%20best%20coffee%20producers%20use%20only%20hand-picked%20ripe%20cherries.%20Skins%20are%20removed%2C%20and%20the%20seeds%20are%20dried%20and%20roasted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvesting%20machines%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20don't%20discern%20between%20ripe%20and%20unripe%20cherries%2C%20gathering%20both%20and%20processing%20them%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20many%20steps%20in%20the%20coffee%20supply%20chain%20make%20the%20origin%20of%20beans%20hard%20to%20track%2C%20but%20reputable%20roasters%20and%20organizations%20like%20the%20Specialty%20Coffee%20Association%20can%20help%20identify%20quality%20product.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESaffron%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221081%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Saffron%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f787ef781926001911a777%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22810%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESaffron%2C%20the%20world's%20most%20expensive%20spice%2C%20comes%20from%20the%20strands%2C%20or%20stigmas%2C%20of%20the%20Crocus%20Sativus%20flower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarmers%20in%20Kashmir%20take%20two%20years%20to%20grow%20flowers%20and%20harvest%20them%2C%20needing%20150%2C000%20flowers%20to%20yield%20a%20kilogram%20of%20saffron%2C%20which%20is%20worth%20about%20%243%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20labor-intensive%20process%2C%20in%20which%20stigmas%20must%20be%20removed%20by%20hand%2C%20snipped%2C%20and%20sorted.%20Fraudsters%20seek%20to%20imitate%20the%20product%20with%20red-dyed%20hay%2C%20horsehair%2C%20coconut%20filaments%2C%20or%20plant%20roots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kashmiri%20government%C2%A0%20has%20even%20introduced%20a%20trading%20center%20with%20a%20geographical%20indicator%20(GI)%20tag%20to%20certify%20authenticity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20caviar%2C%20a%20water%20test%20can%20reveal%20what's%20real%20and%20what%20is%20fake%3A%20real%20saffron%20slowly%20releases%20a%20yellow%20color%20into%20the%20water%2C%20while%20the%20yellowing%20is%20almost%20instant%20with%20artificial%20versions.%20Real%20saffron%20also%20disintegrates%20easily%2C%20while%20fake%20stays%20intact%20after%20wetting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPaying%20more%20for%20products%20does%20not%20assure%20their%20validity%2C%20but%20paying%20less%20kind%20of%20assures%20their%20invalidity%20%E2%80%94%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20cheap%20saffron%2C%26quot%3B%20Larry%20Olmstead%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-faked-foods-in-the-world-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693948909000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f787541b7ced0019c88319%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-faked-foods-in-the-world-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Criminals%20and%20legitimate%20companies%20alike%20make%20big%20bucks%20selling%20less%20expensive%20substitutes%20for%20genuine%20honey%2C%20olive%20oil%2C%20Parmesan%20cheese%2C%20and%20more.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22dreuter%40insider.com%20(Dominick%20Reuter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-faked-foods-in-the-world-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sand%20dredging%20devastating%20ocean%20floor%2C%20UN%20warns%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693948634000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F6C79%2Fproduction%2F_130996772_mediaitem130996768.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-66724628%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Around%20six%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20