FLone-300x300.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F05225147%2FLone-300x300.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F05225147%2FLone-150x150.png%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F05225147%2FLone.png%20621w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-671590%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22300%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENational%20Conference%20leader%20Mohammad%20Akbar%20Lone.%20Photo%3A%20Screenshot%20from%20YouTube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMehta%20alleged%20that%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20added%20insult%20to%20injury%2C%20as%20he%20avoided%20making%20clear%20his%20opposition%20to%20terrorism%20or%20separatist%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%20the%20bench%20will%20analyse%20the%20affidavit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20in%20response%20to%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20concerns%20over%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20and%20its%20silence%20over%20his%20opposition%20to%20terrorism%20and%20separatism%2C%20senior%20counsel%20Kapil%20Sibal%20asked%20the%20bench%20to%20make%20such%20affidavits%20mandatory%20for%20every%20petitioner%20and%20intervener%20before%20the%20court%2C%20to%20avoid%20discrimination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%20expressed%20his%20concern%20that%20the%20SG%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20against%20Lone%20would%20mean%20that%20filing%20a%20petition%20in%20this%20case%20is%20pushing%20a%20separatist%20agenda%20and%20the%20counsel%20arguing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioners%20are%20backing%20a%20similar%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%2C%20however%2C%20intervened%20to%20say%20that%20nobody%20has%20said%20that%20the%20filing%20of%20the%20petition%20constitutes%20a%20separatist%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EToday%E2%80%99s%20arguments%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20representing%20the%20petitioners%20made%20their%20rejoinder%20submissions%20in%20response%20to%20the%20arguments%20of%20the%20Union%20government%20and%20the%20interveners%20supporting%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20pointedly%20asked%20did%20the%20Union%20government%20convert%20a%20state%20into%20a%20union%20territory%20even%20though%20it%20was%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20national%20security%20concern%20is%20a%20ground%2C%20then%20Article%203%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20enabling%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20reorganise%20a%20state%20%E2%80%93%20cannot%20be%20the%20solution%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20bench%20should%20not%20read%20Article%20370%20%E2%80%93%20before%20it%20was%20read%20down%20%E2%80%93%20literally%2C%20and%20infer%20reasons%20for%20the%20usage%20of%20different%20words%20like%20concurrence%2C%20consultation%20and%20recommendation%20in%20different%20contexts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20absurd%20to%20say%20that%20for%20abrogating%20the%20Article%2C%20consultation%20or%20concurrence%20is%20not%20required%2C%20while%20for%20applying%20individual%20Articles%20they%20would%20apply%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20constitution%E2%80%99s%20framers%20would%20never%20have%20intended%20such%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20also%20questioned%20the%20process%20adopted%20for%20dissolving%20the%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20(J%26amp%3BK)%20state%20assembly.%20Citing%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F60799%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ES.R.%20Bommai%20v%20Union%20of%20India%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%C2%A0he%20said%20the%20state%20assembly%20can%20be%20dissolved%20only%20after%20the%20proclamation%20imposing%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20is%20accepted%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Findia-supreme-court-people-centric-polyvocal-image%5C%22%3EIf%20Supreme%20Court%20Has%20to%20Remain%20People-Centric%2C%20It%20Has%20to%20Shed%20Its%20Polyvocal%20Image%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20dissolution%20happened%20without%20the%20aid%20and%20advice%20of%20the%20council%20of%20ministers%2C%20which%20is%20worse%2C%20he%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20anomaly%20that%20he%20pointed%20to%20was%20the%20imposition%20of%20president%E2%80%99s%20rule%20during%20the%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20when%20there%20was%20no%20question%20of%20failure%20of%20the%20constitutional%20machinery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20whole%20motive%20and%20process%20were%20political%2C%20but%20the%20end%20result%20was%20unconstitutional%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20while%20summing%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAmbedkar%E2%80%99s%20fear%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20right.%20He%20said%20that%20he%20could%20not%20rule%20out%20the%20article%20being%20used%20for%20political%20reasons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESibal%20also%20disagreed%20that%20silences%20in%20the%20constitution%20can%20be%20interpreted%20to%20justify%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20exercise%20of%20power%20to%20read%20down%20Article%20370%20in%20the%20manner%20it%20was%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20Rajeev%20Dhavan%20submitted%20that%20Article%203%20is%20a%20mandatory%20provision%20which%20says%20that%20one%20must%20circulate%20any%20Bill%20for%20reorganisation%20to%20the%20concerned%20state%E2%80%99s%20legislature.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20described%20Article%20370%20as%20a%20compromise%20which%20should%20be%20understood%20along%20with%20other%20compromises%20in%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20namely%2C%20Sikhs%20being%20allowed%20to%20carry%20kirpans%2C%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F631708%2F%5C%22%3EExplanation%201%20to%20Article%2025%3C%2Fa%3E)%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mea.gov.in%2FImages%2Fpdf1%2FS6.pdf%5C%22%3ESixth%20Schedule%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%20Getting%20rid%20of%20these%20compromises%20requires%20constitutional%20amendments%2C%20he%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDhavan%20also%20suggested%20that%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98concurrence%E2%80%99%2C%20%E2%80%98consultation%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98recommendation%E2%80%99%20have%20been%20used%20in%20Article%20370%20and%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20constitution%20to%20facilitate%20cooperative%20federalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20counsel%20Dushyant%20Dave%20asked%20whether%20the%20Union%20government%2C%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20law%20declared%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20can%20say%20that%20Article%20370%20ceased%20to%20operate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECiting%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1120103%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBerubari%20v%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20said%20the%20right%20way%20to%20undo%20a%20treaty%20is%20only%20through%20a%20constitutional%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDave%20expressed%20his%20concern%20that%20if%20constitutional%20morality%20is%20allowed%20to%20be%20trampled%2C%20then%20nothing%20will%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Subramanium%20contended%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20a%20self-controlled%20Article%20whose%20fate%20did%20not%20depend%20on%20its%20marginal%20note%2C%20describing%20it%20as%20a%20temporary%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20submitted%20that%20the%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20(IoA)%20did%20not%20lead%20to%20the%20complete%20transfer%20of%20sovereignty.%20It%20is%20because%20Article%20370%20referred%20to%20the%20IoA%20and%20the%20state%20constituent%20assembly%20as%20well%2C%20he%20suggested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20constitution%20bench%20is%20likely%20to%20deliver%20its%20verdict%20in%20the%20case%20before%20December%2025%2C%20when%20Justice%20Sanjay%20Kishan%20Kaul%20%E2%80%93%20a%20senior%20member%20of%20the%20five-judge%20bench%20which%20heard%20the%20case%20for%2016%20days%20%E2%80%93%20retires.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693935131000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F09%2F02131830%2Fthequint_2015-11_a2aacd88-1d34-47fe-b4fd-b96a7918a97a_Supreme-Court_Reuters.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-reserves-verdict-in-article-370-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20put%20a%20lid%20on%20the%20controversy%20over%20petitioner-cum-Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Akbar%20Lone%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20by%20making%20it%20clear%20he%20cannot%20be%20denied%20his%20Article%2032%20rights.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-reserves-verdict-in-article-370-case%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Lighthouse%20Advisors%20India%20sells%201.3%25%20stake%20in%20Bikaji%20Foods%20for%20Rs%20156%20cr%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693933520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Fhp%2Fhome-page%2F2021-02%2F21%2Ffull%2F1613901962-8207.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flighthouse-advisors-india-sells-1-3-stake-in-bikaji-foods-for-rs-156-cr-123090501317_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Mumbai-based%20Lighthouse%20Advisors%20India%20on%20Tuesday%20divested%20a%201.3%20per%20cent%20stake%20in%20Bikaji%20Foods%20International%20for%20nearly%20Rs%20156%20crore%20through%20an%20open%20market%20transaction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Flighthouse-advisors-india-sells-1-3-stake-in-bikaji-foods-for-rs-156-cr-123090501317_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.